    <h4>Calvin</h4>
    <p>The Dame 4 featured a full length Bounce cushion system. This was one of the better renditions of Bounce that I have been able to try, but it still left me hoping
        for more. The Bounce cushioning setup in the Dame 4 is obviously much stiffer than Boost. However, I found it to provide a lot of spring back, something that Boost
        takes away through it's softness and impact protection. Bounce allows for more of that springy feeling where you feel like you are directly putting force into the ground. 
        The impact protection also gets the job done. Overall, the Dame 4's cushioning system was good, but not great. I still feel like Zoom Air is a better setup. 
    </p>
